<Link id="l00088" /><CodeLine lineNumber="88"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">struct</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvmmcjitcompileroptions">LLVMMCJITCompilerOptions</a> &#42;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/debuginfo/lib/debuginfo/logicalview/lib/debuginfo/logicalview/core/lvoptions-cpp/#ab4088b7a11f3cbc38ac16a6e9c72494e">Options</a>, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">size&#95;t</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> SizeOfOptions);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00089" /><CodeLine lineNumber="89"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00090" /><CodeLine lineNumber="90"><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00091" /><CodeLine lineNumber="91"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; Create an MCJIT execution engine for a module, with the given options. It is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00092" /><CodeLine lineNumber="92"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; the responsibility of the caller to ensure that all fields in Options up to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00093" /><CodeLine lineNumber="93"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; the given SizeOfOptions are initialized. It is correct to pass a smaller</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00094" /><CodeLine lineNumber="94"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; value of SizeOfOptions that omits some fields. The canonical way of using</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00095" /><CodeLine lineNumber="95"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; this is:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00096" /><CodeLine lineNumber="96"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00097" /><CodeLine lineNumber="97"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; LLVMMCJITCompilerOptions options;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00098" /><CodeLine lineNumber="98"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; LLVMInitializeMCJITCompilerOptions(&amp;options, sizeof(options));</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00099" /><CodeLine lineNumber="99"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; ... fill in those options you care about</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00100" /><CodeLine lineNumber="100"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; LLVMCreateMCJITCompilerForModule(&amp;jit, mod, &amp;options, sizeof(options),</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00101" /><CodeLine lineNumber="101"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;                                  &amp;error);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00102" /><CodeLine lineNumber="102"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00103" /><CodeLine lineNumber="103"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; Note that this is also correct, though possibly suboptimal:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00104" /><CodeLine lineNumber="104"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00105" /><CodeLine lineNumber="105"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; LLVMCreateMCJITCompilerForModule(&amp;jit, mod, 0, 0, &amp;error);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00106" /><CodeLine lineNumber="106"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00107" /><CodeLine lineNumber="107"><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/groups/llvmcsupporttypes/#ga209de0bceb13179a973c6a45211617bd">LLVMBool</a> <a href="/docs/api/groups/llvmcexecutionengine/#gaa97dff3ed910ce2e0fc7c96b50b1c897">LLVMCreateMCJITCompilerForModule</a>(</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00169" /><CodeLine lineNumber="169"><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00170" /><CodeLine lineNumber="170"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; Create a simple custom MCJIT memory manager. This memory manager can</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00171" /><CodeLine lineNumber="171"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; intercept allocations in a module-oblivious way. This will return NULL</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00172" /><CodeLine lineNumber="172"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; if any of the passed functions are NULL.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00173" /><CodeLine lineNumber="173"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00174" /><CodeLine lineNumber="174"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; @param Opaque An opaque client object to pass back to the callbacks.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="175"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; @param AllocateCodeSection Allocate a block of memory for executable code.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00176" /><CodeLine lineNumber="176"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; @param AllocateDataSection Allocate a block of memory for data.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00177" /><CodeLine lineNumber="177"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; @param FinalizeMemory Set page permissions and flush cache. Return 0 on</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00178" /><CodeLine lineNumber="178"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;   success, 1 on error.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00179" /><CodeLine lineNumber="179"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
